","    'figure.titlesize': 16\n","})\n","\n","# Load the localized panel data (REPLACE THE PATH BELOW)\n","file_path = '/kaggle/input/datasets/rabbani0123/pakistan-air-quality-annual-summary-2015-2025/pakistan_air_quality_annual_summary.csv'\n","df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n","\n","# Quick validation of dataset structural integrity\n","print(f\"Dataset successfully initialized. Total Records: {df.shape[0]}, Total Features: {df.shape[1]}\")\n","display(df.head())"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"8b1bc707","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.002437,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.376816+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.374379+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## 1. Geographic Polarization: The Punjab Smog Belt\n","\n","Air pollution profiles across Pakistan are heavily influenced by local geography, industrial density, and transboundary meteorology. By filtering our data to the most recent comprehensive cross-section (2025), we can map the stark spatial disparities that exist between provinces. \n","\n","We define the strict World Health Organization safe annual exposure threshold ($5.0 \\ \\mu g/m^3$) as our scientific baseline."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"24236d45","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.38255Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.382205Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.849201Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.848354Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.472075,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.851236+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.379161+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["# Filter and sort the cross-sectional data for 2025\n","df_2025 = df[df['year'] == 2025].sort_values(by='pm25_annual_avg', ascending=False)\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n","\n","# Highlight Punjab cities dynamically to expose the geographic cluster\n","colors = ['#C0392B' if x == 'Punjab' else '#34495E' for x in df_2025['province']]\n","bars = plt.bar(df_2025['city'], df_2025['pm25_annual_avg'], color=colors, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.85)\n","\n","# Add the WHO guideline reference anchor\n","plt.axhline(y=5.0, color='#2980B9', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=r'WHO Safe Annual Threshold ($5.0 \\ \\mu g/m^3$)')\n","\n","# Annotate values directly on top of bars for immediate analytical clarity\n","for bar in bars:\n","    height = bar.get_height()\n","    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height + 2, f'{height:.1f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\n","\n","plt.title('Urban Spatial Disparity: Annual Average PM2.5 Concentrations (2025)', pad=15, fontweight='bold')\n","plt.ylabel(r'Annual Mean $PM_{2.5}$ Concentration ($\\mu g/m^3$)')\n","plt.xlabel('Urban Sampling Center')\n","plt.xticks(rotation=30)\n","plt.legend(frameon=True, facecolor='white')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"409aecc1","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.002261,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.856206+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.853945+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## 2. Atmospheric Compounding: The Winter Inversion Multiplier\n","\n","Evaluating annual mean values alone can cloud the short-term physiological dangers faced by urban populations. During late autumn and winter, colder ground temperatures compress the atmospheric boundary layer, trapping vehicular and industrial emissions close to the surface. \n","\n","To visualize this transition from summer baseline lows to peak winter spikes, we construct a descriptive dumbbell plot mapping the minimum monthly average directly against the peak winter monthly average for each city."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"e277c68d","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.862451Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.862155Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.060104Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.059181Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.203045,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.061533+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:13.858488+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x700 with 1 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["# Sort cities by their peak exposure levels to preserve layout hierarchy\n","city_seasonal = df[df['year'] == 2025].sort_values(by='pm25_peak_month', ascending=True)\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12, 7))\n","y_range = range(1, len(city_seasonal) + 1)\n","\n","# Generate structural link lines between data points\n","plt.hlines(y=y_range, xmin=city_seasonal['pm25_min_month'], xmax=city_seasonal['pm25_peak_month'], \n","           color='#BDC3C7', linestyle='-', linewidth=2.5, alpha=0.6)\n","\n","# Plot scatter distributions representing the seasonal shift\n","plt.scatter(city_seasonal['pm25_min_month'], y_range, color='#2ECC71', s=100, label='Annual Minimum Month Exposure', zorder=3, edgecolor='black')\n","plt.scatter(city_seasonal['pm25_peak_month'], y_range, color='#E74C3C', s=100, label='Peak Winter Inversion Exposure', zorder=3, edgecolor='black')\n","\n","plt.yticks(y_range, city_seasonal['city'])\n","plt.xlabel(r'Particulate Concentration Thresholds ($\\mu g/m^3$)')\n","plt.title('The Winter Inversion Effect: Seasonal Multipliers Across Urban Centers (2025)', pad=15, fontweight='bold')\n","plt.legend(loc='lower right', frameon=True)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"3f98fb7d","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.002844,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.067711+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.064867+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## 3. Historical Trajectories & Predictive Modeling (To 2030)\n","\n","To assess whether existing localized atmospheric conditions are improving, deteriorating, or stabilizing, we isolate four distinct sentinel hubs representing different populations and baseline pollution loads:\n","* **Faisalabad & Lahore:** Core industrial/agricultural zones in the Punjab Smog Belt.\n","* **Karachi:** Coastal megacity benefiting from maritime air clearing.\n","* **Islamabad:** Northern capital characterized by localized green spaces and alternative topography.\n","\n","We train an Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) Linear Regression model on the 2015–2025 historical series to project the ambient linear trend line up to 2030."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"c448dc5e","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.076229Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.075937Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.343668Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.34275Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.274813,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.345593+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.07078+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1300x700 with 1 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["plt.figure(figsize=(13, 7))\n","\n","sentinel_cities = ['Faisalabad', 'Lahore', 'Karachi', 'Islamabad']\n","future_years = np.array(range(2026, 2031)).reshape(-1, 1)\n","palette = {'Faisalabad': '#7D6608', 'Lahore': '#78281F', 'Karachi': '#1B4F72', 'Islamabad': '#145A32'}\n","\n","for city in sentinel_cities:\n","    city_data = df[df['city'] == city].sort_values('year')\n","    X_hist = city_data['year'].values.reshape(-1, 1)\n","    y_hist = city_data['pm25_annual_avg'].values\n","    \n","    # Render underlying historical data points\n","    line = plt.plot(city_data['year'], y_hist, marker='o', linewidth=2, color=palette[city], label=f'{city} (Observed History)')\n","    \n","    # Train the OLS Linear Regression Model\n","    model = LinearRegression().fit(X_hist, y_hist)\n","    y_pred = model.predict(future_years)\n","    \n","    # Render forecast trajectory lines\n","    plt.plot(range(2026, 2031), y_pred, linestyle=':', linewidth=2.5, color=palette[city], alpha=0.85, label=f'{city} (2026-2030 Trend Projection)')\n","\n","# Add absolute critical threshold comparison line\n","plt.axhline(y=5.0, color='#C0392B', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5, label='WHO Target Baseline Limit (5.0 µg/m³)')\n","\n","plt.title(r'Empirical $PM_{2.5}$ Historical Trends & Linear Regression Projections (To 2030)', pad=15, fontweight='bold')\n","plt.xlabel('Calendar Year Target')\n","plt.ylabel(r'Annual Mean $PM_{2.5}$ Concentration ($\\mu g/m^3$)')\n","plt.xlim(2015, 2030)\n","plt.xticks(range(2015, 2031, 2))\n","plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.35, 1.0), frameon=True)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"ed4d2494","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003987,"end_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.354095+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-05-21T15:05:14.350108+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["---\n","### References & Methodological Notes\n","1. **World Health Organization (WHO) Guidelines:** The baseline threshold of $5.0 \\ \\mu g/m^3$ utilized in this analysis reflects the updated 2021 WHO Global Air Quality Guidelines (AQGs) for long-term ambient particulate matter exposure.\n","2. **Predictive Constraints:** The Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) regression utilized for the 2026-2030 projections assumes a linear continuation of localized industrial, agricultural, and meteorological patterns. It does not account for sudden, unannounced macroscopic policy interventions."]}],"metadata":{"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"databundleVersionId":17326184,"datasetId":10472452,"sourceId":16336524,"sourceType":"datasetVersion"}],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isGpuEnabled":false,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook"},"ker